    "title": "Liberty Forever (1776 - 2020 - ????)",
    "description": "&quot;Patriotism is a lively sense of collective responsibility. Nationalism is a silly cock crowing on its own dunghill.&quot;\n– Richard Aldington, The Colonel’s Daughter (1931)\n\n&quot;The nationalism of a great nation inevitably degenerates into chauvinism and imperialism. The nationalism of a small nation is aimed primarily at the survival of the nation among others.&quot;\n– Vasil Bykau, Правілы жыцця Васіля Быкава\n\n&quot;The flames kindled on the 4th of July 1776, have spread over too much of the globe to be extinguished by the feeble engines of despotism; on the contrary, they will consume these engines and all who work them.&quot;\n– Thomas Jefferson, in a letter to John Adams (12 September 1821).\n\n&quot;A swarm of bees in May is worth a load of hay.\nA swarm of bees in June is worth a silver spoon.\nA swarm of bees in July is not worth a fly.&quot;\n– English proverb",
